The For Product model changes how and why we work and own
to resolve the conflict between abundance and finance.

Product TicketğŸ« represents some future good or service.
Source Titleâ–¦ represents fractional ownership in land or a fixed asset.
Work AgreementğŸ“ƒ represents contract obligation for a future service.

Users may:
. Buy Product TicketsğŸ« representing future products.
. Sign Work AgreementsğŸ“ƒ for Source Titlesâ–¦ which vest as work is complete.
. Buy Product TicketsğŸ« representing surplus products.

The system must:
Sell  Product TicketsğŸ« to buy the sources to get production started.
Grant limited source access to those who sign Work AgreementsğŸ“ƒ.  Issue expiring ğŸ”‘ here.
Vest source ownership to those who complete Work AgreementsğŸ“ƒ.  Issue Source Titlesâ–¦ here.
Sell surplus Product TicketsğŸ« to buy more sources and onboard more workers.
Use Source Titlesâ–¦ and Work AgreementsğŸ“ƒ to pre-allocate goods and services.

== COMMENTARY
We can make businesses owned by the
consumers who need those products
to regain control of production
and make price equal cost.

For example, if you own an avocado tree,
you own those avocados without purchase,
even if someone else or ğŸ¤– does the work.

This is a generalization of Wikipedia.org/wiki/Imputed_rent

By combining the roles of consumer and owner,
purchase disappears, and those profits with it.

When consumer is owner, there is no sale and no profit.
Of course every worker is also a consumer.

